            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>Improving air-quality prediction in the Uinta Basin region. We aim for accessible public outreach and risk communication for stakeholders and public alike.</p>
            
            <h2>Research Focus</h2>
            <p>Predicting air quality in the Uinta Basin (winter ozone). Artificial intelligence: machine learning, large-language models (LLMs). Risk communication.</p>
            
            <h2>Public Engagement</h2>
            <p>We want to make science accessible. Through plain-language spotlight posts and educational videos, the team hopes its work can be explained more accessibly.</p>
            
            <h2>Collaboration</h2>
            <p>The BRC and Lawson Group comprise professors, technical staff, undergraduate and graduate students, and high-school research assistants. We work with community partners to meet the Basin economy's environmental needs and public awareness of our work.</p>

            <h2>Support and funding</h2>
            <p>Our team's work is supported by the Uintah Co. Special Service District 1 and the Utah Legislature and is entirely non-partisan.
